BFN 

  [Text] At 0830 this morning, Foreign Minister Squadron 
Leader Prasong Sunsiri accompanied Faruq Qaddumi, the foreign 
affairs minister of the Palestinian Liberation Organization, to 
pay a courtesy call on Prime Minister Chuan Likphai at 
Government House. 
  Following the courtesy call, the Thai foreign minister 
reported that the PLO foreign minister summarized the major 
events in the Middle East for the Thai prime minister. The Thai 
prime minister expressed his wish that all problems would be 
solved successfully in order to establish peace in that region. 
  [Begin Prasong recording] The prime minister said he 
supports 
all of the peace processes, which are in conformity with the 
agreement. The PLO foreign minister also informed the prime 
minister that PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat conveyed his regards to 
Prime Minister Chuan. In reply, our prime minister extended his 
regards to the PLO leader. In addition, the Thai prime minister 
informed the PLO foreign minister that Thailand would like the 
opportunity to welcome an official visit to Thailand by Yasir 
'Arafat in the future. [end recording] 

